              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma rays were detected using GRETINA (Gamma-",
                "Ray Energy Tracking In-beam Nuclear Array) detectors",
                "positioned at laboratory angles of 58deg and 90deg."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The projectile-like reaction products were",
                "identified with the S800 spectrograph downstream of",
                "the GRETINA setup. The S800 was run in focused mode",
                "in order to allow a large momentum acceptance. 31S15+",
                "ions were clearly separated from other reaction",
                "products, and a nearly 100 % acceptance at the S800",
                "focal plane was determined."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Data acquisition was triggered by",
                "coincidences between GRETINA and the first",
                "scintillator at the focal plane of the S800.",
                "Downscaled projectile-like singles events were also",
                "accepted for minimum bias analysis"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 30MeV/u 30P15+ beam was produced inflight via",
                "fragmentation reactions using a primary beam of",
                "150MeV/u, 112 pnA 36Ar18+ ions to bombard a",
                "1857mg/cm2 thick Be target. The A1900 high-resolution",
                "fragment separator selected the ions of interest",
                "based on the momentum/charge, p/q, ratio after they",
                "had passed through a 450mg/cm2 thick Al wedge The",
                "26Al beam had a high purity (97+-2)% and an average",
                "intensity of (1.04+-0.08)E+6 particles per second."
              ]
            }
          ],
